## Alternative: VPS Deployment Guide

### System Requirements

**Minimum Requirements:**
- Ubuntu 20.04 / 22.04 LTS
- 2 GB RAM (4 GB recommended)
- 2 CPU cores
- 20 GB storage (40 GB recommended)
- PostgreSQL 12+
- Python 3.8+

### Installation Steps

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á - Server Preparation

```bash
# System update
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install dependencies
sudo apt install -y \
    postgresql \
    postgresql-client \
    python3-pip \
    python3-dev \
    python3-venv \
    libxml2-dev \
    libxslt1-dev \
    libldap2-dev \
    libsasl2-dev \
    libssl-dev \
    libjpeg-dev \
    libpq-dev \
    git \
    build-essential \
    wget \
    node-less \
    npm

# Install wkhtmltopdf (for PDF reports)
wget https://github.com/wkhtmltopdf/packaging/releases/download/0.12.6-1/wkhtmltox_0.12.6-1.focal_amd64.deb
sudo apt install -y ./wkhtmltox_0.12.6-1.focal_amd64.deb
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á‚ - PostgreSQL Setup

```bash
# PostgreSQL user create
sudo -u postgres createuser -s odoo
sudo -u postgres createdb odoo

# Set password (optional)
sudo -u postgres psql
ALTER USER odoo WITH PASSWORD 'your_password';
\q
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º áƒ - Odoo User Creation

```bash
# Create system user for Odoo
sudo adduser --system --home=/opt/odoo --group odoo

# Create directories
sudo mkdir /var/log/odoo
sudo chown odoo:odoo /var/log/odoo
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á„ - Odoo Installation

**Method A: From Source (Recommended for Flexibility)**

```bash
# Switch to odoo user
sudo su - odoo -s /bin/bash

# Clone Odoo repository
git clone https://github.com/odoo/odoo.git --depth 1 --branch 17.0 /opt/odoo/odoo

# Create Python virtual environment
python3 -m venv /opt/odoo/venv

# Activate virtual environment
source /opt/odoo/venv/bin/activate

# Install Python dependencies
pip3 install wheel
pip3 install -r /opt/odoo/odoo/requirements.txt

# Exit odoo user
exit
```

**Method B: Package Installation (Simpler)**

```bash
# Add Odoo repository
wget -O - https://nightly.odoo.com/odoo.key | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb http://nightly.odoo.com/17.0/nightly/deb/ ./" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/odoo.list

# Install Odoo
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y odoo
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á… - Configuration File

**Create configuration file:**

```bash
sudo nano /etc/odoo.conf
```

**Configuration content:**

```ini
[options]
; Basic Settings
admin_passwd = strong_admin_password_here
db_host = localhost
db_port = 5432
db_user = odoo
db_password = your_db_password

; Paths
addons_path = /opt/odoo/odoo/addons
data_dir = /opt/odoo/.local/share/Odoo

; Logging
logfile = /var/log/odoo/odoo.log
log_level = info

; Server
http_port = 8069
xmlrpc_port = 8069

; Workers (for production)
workers = 2
max_cron_threads = 1

; Limits
limit_memory_hard = 2684354560
limit_memory_soft = 2147483648
limit_request = 8192
limit_time_cpu = 600
limit_time_real = 1200
```

**Set proper permissions:**

```bash
sudo chown odoo:odoo /etc/odoo.conf
sudo chmod 640 /etc/odoo.conf
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á† - Systemd Service Setup

**Create service file:**

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/odoo.service
```

**Service content:**

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Odoo
Documentation=http://www.odoo.com
After=network.target postgresql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=odoo
Group=odoo
ExecStart=/opt/odoo/venv/bin/python3 /opt/odoo/odoo/odoo-bin -c /etc/odoo.conf
WorkingDirectory=/opt/odoo
StandardOutput=journal+console

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

**Enable and start service:**

```bash
# Reload systemd
sudo systemctl daemon-reload

# Enable Odoo service
sudo systemctl enable odoo

# Start Odoo
sudo systemctl start odoo

# Check status
sudo systemctl status odoo

# View logs
sudo journalctl -u odoo -f
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á‡ - Nginx Setup (Optional but Recommended)

**Install Nginx:**

```bash
sudo apt install -y nginx
```

**Create Nginx configuration:**

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/odoo
```

**Nginx configuration:**

```nginx
upstream odoo {
    server 127.0.0.1:8069;
}

upstream odoochat {
    server 127.0.0.1:8072;
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name your-domain.com;

    # Proxy settings
    proxy_read_timeout 720s;
    proxy_connect_timeout 720s;
    proxy_send_timeout 720s;

    # Log files
    access_log /var/log/nginx/odoo-access.log;
    error_log /var/log/nginx/odoo-error.log;

    # Redirect requests to Odoo backend
    location / {
        proxy_redirect off;
        proxy_pass http://odoo;

        # Headers
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }

    # WebSocket for live chat
    location /websocket {
        proxy_pass http://odoochat;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }

    # Cache static files
    location ~* /web/static/ {
        proxy_cache_valid 200 90m;
        proxy_buffering on;
        expires 864000;
        proxy_pass http://odoo;
    }

    # Gzip compression
    gzip_types text/css text/scss text/plain text/xml application/xml application/json application/javascript;
    gzip on;
}
```

**Enable site:**

```bash
# Create symbolic link
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/odoo /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

# Remove default site
sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default

# Test configuration
sudo nginx -t

# Restart Nginx
sudo systemctl restart nginx
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º áˆ - SSL Setup with Let's Encrypt (Optional)

```bash
# Install Certbot
sudo apt install -y certbot python3-certbot-nginx

# Obtain SSL certificate
sudo certbot --nginx -d your-domain.com

# Auto-renewal (already enabled by default)
sudo systemctl status certbot.timer
```

#### á€¡á€†á€„á€·á€º á‰ - Firewall Setup

```bash
# Allow SSH, HTTP, HTTPS
sudo ufw allow 22/tcp
sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
sudo ufw allow 443/tcp

# Enable firewall
sudo ufw enable

# Check status
sudo ufw status
```

### Post-Installation Steps

#### Access Odoo

1. **Open browser:**
   - With Nginx: `http://your-domain.com`
   - Without Nginx: `http://your-vps-ip:8069`

2. **Create database:**
   - Master Password: (á€á€„á€º set á€œá€¯á€•á€ºá€‘á€¬á€¸á€á€±á€¬ admin_passwd)
   - Database Name: production
   - Email: admin@yourcompany.com
   - Password: strong password
   - Language: English
   - Country: Myanmar
   - Demo data: Unchecked

3. **Install Accounting app**

